        <label style="margin: 20px auto;">15 April, 2020</label>
        <p class="ptext1">One major criticism of charity runs, hikes and cycles is that people simply do something they were already going to do for fun and part with a little money to feel even better about it. Perhaps less fun: donating time to do something you’re actually good at. The catchily titled 8 Hours’ Overtime For A Good Cause tries to harness that idea by organising volunteers to collaboratively support local charities.
        </p>
      </div>
